Really good! I wish i would have read reviews before i made it, it definitely did not need 1 cup of sugar. I put in about 3/4 cup and i still would have preferred less. I also threw poblano and red peppers in the food processor and folded them in, they added a lot more flavor instead of just topping with them. In addition to the peppers for topping i added cheese and breadcrumbs, and used twice as much cheese when folding it in. All in all, it was delicious and everyone loved it. i almost considered not beating the egg whites, but did and everyone loved the texture. And it looked like a souffle and have a nice crust. Another bit that i wish i would have read in advance: not rinsing the roasted poblanos, instead putting them in a bag and then removing the charred skin. I don't cook with them much and didn't realize how mild they get after rinsing. This recipe will probably become a regular!

