GREAT success! I made this at the last minute for Xmas dinner (my mom wanted a corn pudding). It was fantastic. I used less sugar per reviews, but only a bit less. I also didn't have whole milk, so instead, in grinding the corn, I used a little bit of skim milk and the rest was reduced fat sour cream. I also added shredded asiago cheese on top-- I think having sprinkled cheese on top is crucial because it creates a nice cheesy / crusty finish. Also, didn't have a red pepper or poblano chile, so used one jalapeno and a bit of pickled pepper (red and yellow) which worked out fine. It was a huge hit and super easy to make; also very adaptable to change. Will definitely make it again-- ASAP.

