Rating: 4
I live in Austin and get to enjoy Fonda San Miguel on a regular basis. I was so excited when the cookbook came out and included the corn pudding. All I can say is this recipe is always a big hit at dinner parties. I follow the recipe almost exactly, using frozen cut corn. The only change I make is that I use a bit less sugar. Frozen corn is often quite sweet unto itself. If you do not have the time to roast the poblano, you can get almost the same effect by simply slicing the poblano in long strips and sauteing quickly, skin-side down, in a very wee bit of oil. Use two forks to slip off the skin before placing the strips. However, if you have time, roasting the pepper is preferable; it adds flavor. I place the green and red strips on in alternating colors. Before trying out reviewers suggestions, I encourage you to follow this recipe to the letter so you can draw your own conclusions. And, if you come to Austin, be sure to make reservations for Sunday brunch at Fonda San Miguel. Outstanding!

