This dish was a big hit at Thanksgiving dinner. I used a cubanelle pepper instead of the poblano, as I couldn't find a poblano at my grocery, but otherwise followed the directions as written. Depending on the height of the dish you are cooking it in, you may need to add some time to the cooking. I used a 12" by 7" and it took about an hour to cook. But when it came out, it was worth it. It looked great on the dinner table, and tasted great as well. As stated in the recipe, the pudding/souffle will sink after 15-20 minutes out of the oven, so it is definitely important to take this out of the oven at the very last minute before serving.

