Extremely easy and delicious; played to rave reviews by our Thanksgiving guests...I took a few liberties which I strongly recommend. Fold fresh white corn kernels, 1/2 of a red pepper, finely diced and 1/4 c. additional roasted poblano chile, diced into the mixture before baking. I also doubled the amount of cheese and used 1/2 cream and 1/2 milk instead of all milk. Finally, be sure to add a bit of salt and freshly ground black pepper before baking. Sinfully delish!

